  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of this prospective, randomized , blinded study is to compare two different infusion
      techniques (continuous VS intermittent automatic bolus) to assess the effects of
      postoperative analgesia after Day-Case anterior cruciate ligament (ACL) reconstruction.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
